ED  - Dhawan, A. K.
TI  - Transforming crop breeding and seed systems: maize in the tropics as a case study.
T2  - Transforming agrifood systems in the face of climate changes and energy transitions. Proceedings of the Indian Ecological Society International Conference (IESIC), Punjab Agricultural University, Ludhiana, India, 12-15 November 2024
M3  - Conference paper
AB  - Transforming plant breeding and seed systems is essential to build resilient, sustainable and climate-responsive agrifood systems. This transformation must integrate innovations in genetic diversity, climate-smart agronomic practices and postharvest management to effectively address both biotic and abiotic stresses. A multidisciplinary approach, including precision agriculture, data-driven breeding and advanced phenotyping, is crucial for optimizing cultivar development and seed delivery. Strengthening national and international collaboration, investing in infrastructure and human resources and enabling supportive policies are key to accelerating the adoption of climate-resilient and nutritionally enriched crop cultivars. Inclusive and efficient seed systems, particularly in the Global South, must ensure affordable access to high-quality seeds for smallholders, leveraging digital and genomic technologies for greater impact.
