TI  - Special Issue: Transforming smallholder irrigation systems from dysfunctional to functional climate smart agricultural systems.
T2  - International Journal of Water Resources Development
M3  - Journal issue
AB  - This is the third special issue of the International Journal of Water Resources Development presenting the learnings and results from the Transforming Irrigation in Southern Africa (TISA) project. Eleven papers are presented, in addition to an editorial. The first paper offers an historical analysis of the Green Revolution. The next three papers discuss the impact of the TISA interventions on the pressing need to increase the adaptive capacity of smallholders and their irrigation schemes to climate change. Other papers deal with the impacts of COVID-19 restrictions on farmers from schemes that experienced TISA interventions; the impact of the TISA interventions on underserved groups; the role of youth in the local economy around irrigation schemes; and the two core interventions of soil moisture and nutrients monitoring tools and agricultural innovation platforms (AIPs). The final paper outlines the way forward for further transformation of the schemes engaged in the TISA project.
