AB  - This paper provides information on the amount of damage to Japanese agriculture, forestry and fisheries in the areas affected by the Great East Japan Earthquake and tsunami which occurred on 11 March 2011. The successes of various efforts for the restoration of farmland and agricultural facilities and in the revival of agriculture in the affected prefectures, Iwate, Miyagi and Fukushima, are discussed. Various trends in agricultural management in the 3 affected prefectures are also presented.
