TI  - Special Issue: A systems approach framework for coastal management and its application in practice.
T2  - Journal of Coastal Conservation
M3  - Journal issue
AB  - This special issue introduces an improved and refreshed version of the systems approach framework (SAF), the product of the work developed under the research project BONUS BaltCoast (A Systems Approach Framework for Coastal Research and Management in the Baltic). The first article describes in detail this new version of the SAF. This special issue also tests the new SAF process through several case studies comprised of the BONUS BaltCoast project. In the first study, the SAF is used to explore the possibility, together with stakeholders, to open a beach in the Curonian Lagoon (Lithuania). In the second study, the SAF is applied to evaluate the effects of three potential scenarios of Zebra mussel (Dreissena polymorpha) cultivation in the Oder Lagoon (Germany) in an ecological-social-economic context. In the third study, the SAF is used to support coastal zone management in Parnu (Estonia) by (re)evaluating coastal protection and flood prevention measures; and in the fourth study it is used to support sustainable fisheries management by understanding the decline of Atlantic cod (Gadus morhua) fishery in Danish waters. The last article shows that, in the SAF application, an effective public participation strategy is of great importance to support the process of policy implementation and decision-making.
