AB  - This annual report provides a detailed account of bilateral development cooperation between Norway and 25 of the countries in Africa, Asia, Latin America and the Middle East that received the most assistance in 2006. The report focuses on the results achieved in the priority areas for cooperation and general development trends in the countries concerned, and describes Norway's contribution in this context. The priority areas covered the following: energy resources, good governance and human rights, education, health, legal counselling programmes, election monitoring, reintegration of refugees and child soldiers, peace and reconciliation, agriculture and combating HIV/AIDs, economic reforms, natural resource management, fisheries, food security, gender equality, rural development, and disaster assistance.
