AB  - This paper examines the impact of the 2004 tsunami on fisheries and fishing communities in South Asia; the immediate response to the disaster; and the issues and challenges concerning the post-tsunami rehabilitation of fisheries and aquaculture and coastal zone management. It is suggested that post-tsunami rehabilitation offers the opportunity to build back, improve and make more secure the lives of disadvantaged sections of the population and set fisheries and coastal resource use on a sustainable footing.
