TI  - The role of Fisheries Cooperative Societies in reconstruction process of earthquake affected small villages on the sea: a case study of peninsula areas in Kamaishi City, Iwate.
T2  - Journal of Rural Planning
M3  - Journal article
AB  - The purpose of this research is to investigate the role of fisheries cooperative societies in the reconstruction process of earthquake-affected small villages by the sea. There are numerous fishing villages that have various social and economic backgrounds in the affected areas of the Great East Japan Earthquake. The fisheries cooperative at Hakozaki Peninsula in Kamaishi City carried out various measures required to improve the living standards of local residents before the earthquake. This organizational experience ensured fair and equitable distribution of benefits through joint fishing just after the earthquake.
