AU  - Teufel, Nils
TI  - Index-based livestock insurance to support pastoralists against droughts.
T2  - Food Policy
M3  - Journal article
AB  - This article discusses the development and scaling of index-based livestock insurance (IBLI) in Africa's drylands, highlighting its role in mitigating the impact of droughts on pastoral households. IBLI provides insurance coverage based on remotely sensed data reflecting vegetation conditions, reducing the need for costly data collection and local claims verification. Research articles published in Food Policyhave contributed significantly to the understanding and adoption of IBLI, motivating large public and private investments in the product. Since its launch in 2010, IBLI has been scaled across much of the Horn of Africa, with substantial public investments and policies supporting its growth. Studies have shown that IBLI has positive impacts on clients and has become a proven development tool, with over $100 million in coverage provided to over 200,000 households in 2023. Peer-reviewed research has also influenced supportive policies at various levels, contributing to the scaling and continued market development of IBLI.
