AB  - This issue contains topics on preliminary studies on triploid of yellowtail; application of germplasm preservation in breeding programmes for molluscan shellfish aquaculture and restoration; improving aquaculture production inHaliotisspecies through the development of a genomic toolkit; culture protocols and production of triploid purple-hinge rock scallops; big data in agriculture and the USDA/ARS initiative; genomic selection in aquaculture; genetic selection on animals using pedigree, phenotypic and genomic information; exploring transcriptomic patterns in slow and fast growingSeriola dorsalislarvae; modelling the variable effects of using wild and cultured broodstock on the fitness risk due to escaped farmed fish; interbreeding between farmed coho salmon (Oncorhynchus kisutch) that escaped during the earthquake and tsunami disaster of 2011 with native masu salmon (O. masou); evaluation of the tsunami impact on the genetic diversity of the marbled flounder (Pseudopleuronectes yokohamae) in Sendai Bay, Miyagi, Japan; experimental hybridization and competition between Atlantic salmon (Salmo salar) and native salmonid species in Japan; hybrid striped bass national breeding programme: research towards genetic improvement of a non-model species; production ofBenedenia-resistant yellowtail (Seriola quinqueradiata) families; coho salmon broodstock development: a case study of the Domsea coho salmon and development of improved catfish germplasm at the warmwater aquaculture research unit, DSDA-ARS.
