TI  - Increase of drought resistance of tetraploid populations of maize.
T2  - Vestnik OrelGAU
M3  - Journal article
AB  - Investigations were conducted in Russia during 2007-10 to study the possibility of increase of polymorphism and drought resistance of tetraploid maize populations. The performance of the new tetraploid hybrids were compared with that of the standard diploid hybrid Krasnodarskii 382 MV. Data are tabulated on genetic components of the new tetraploid populations and the frequency of detection of unreduced female gametes. Data are included on characteristics of sources of drought resistance based on fertility of pollen and water suction force of seedlings. Resistance of initial tetraploid populations to water deficit is considered. Data are tabulated on average indicator of seedling emergence, pollen fertility and stability of grain yield in relation to drought resistance of sources of the resistance. Morphological and biological properties and deviation values of morphobiological properties of plants at different soil water contents are compared. Data are tabulated on phenotypic correlation between drought resistance and valuable plant breeding properties of maize. Data are tabulated on variation coefficient of main properties of maize, i.e. grain yield, stem height, cob length, pollen fertility and stem infertility. Crop yield of tetraploid populations in 2008 is outlined. A diagram is presented on regression lines of grain yield. Data are tabulated on the value of ecological plasticity and stability of tetraploid populations of drought resistant maize.
